# .dockerignore — exclude files from the Docker build context
#
# This applies to the @jadeassist/widget Dockerfile build
# (packages/widget/Dockerfile, build context = repo root).
#
# Keeping the context lean speeds up `docker build` and avoids
# accidentally shipping local artifacts into the image.

# Version-control metadata
.git
.gitignore

# Local environment / secrets (never ship into images)
.env
.env.*

# All pre-existing build outputs and installed deps
# (the Dockerfile runs `npm ci` and `npm run build` itself)
node_modules/
packages/*/node_modules/
dist/
packages/*/dist/
build/
*.tsbuildinfo

# Test / example HTML files in the widget package (not needed in the image)
packages/widget/cdn-test.html
packages/widget/example.html
packages/widget/test-*.html

# Documentation
*.md
ARCHITECTURE.md
DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md
GITHUB_DEPLOYMENT.md
QUICK_START.md
RAILWAY.md
README.md

# Editor / OS artifacts
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store

# CI
.github/
